RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAUAI DAN was brushed away from the gate, found running room along the rail entering the stretch, swept the lead and won going away. SIX SHOTS OF T vied outside, gained the advantage in the far turn, was overtaken, and finished up second best. BARAK fanned three-wide, and improved late stretch. LIFES ADVENTURE broke alertly, dropped back through the far turn, and passed a tiring foe deep stretch. FROSTEDBIRD came over leaving the gate causing COOL DOMINION to clip heels, dueled inside of SIX SHOTS OF T in the final turn and came up empty for the drive. COOL DOMINION clipped heels with FROSTEDBIRD away from the gate, trailed and failed to produce a bid. REAL JUSTICE showed little. TAPFERSURE stalked outside, and tired. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of COOL DOMINION against the rider of FROSTEDBIRD alleging interference away from the gate. After review by the Board of Stewards, FROSTEDBIRD was disqualified and placed sixth for interference to COOL DOMINION.

The purse w ill be divided $30,000 to the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the second place finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. A payment of $500.00 will be paid to all horses who st art and finish sixth or worse. The field will be limited to 12 starters. RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG BAD INTAGLIO sat in the second flight, dropped back saving ground in the far turn, was roused at the head of the lane and made a late run outside for the win. LIL ZAPPER quickly went to the front then showed the way through the backstretch, and was challenged by MUDINATOR around the three-sixteenth marker, clung to the lead under encouragement but was denied late. MUDINATOR chased from the four path, loomed boldly near the three-sixteenth pole, but was unable to muster the bid that was needed. VIRAL was not a factor. KISS ME HELLO chased the pacesetter from the four path, and tired early.
